Standard curves were performed using nucleic acids prepared from a serial dilution series of both a ZIKV-infected TCF stock (1 × 107 PFU/ml) and IVT RNA (107 to 0.1 IVT RNA copies/μl). Pearson correlation coefficients (R
2) were used to assess curve fitness. PCR amplification efficiencies (%) were calculated using the following formula: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
